"he had the ghastly feeling that he had let a priceless diamond slip through his fingers. he had, and in her own way so had she. but she was willing to live with the loss. she had ajusted to it, and she had no desire to reopen old wounds."

["what if it worked this time", he asked hopefully, wanting to convince her. " but what if it didnt?, we'd both get hurt. way too much" she tried to convince herself she didnt want him, but she did of course, but she didnt want the pain that would inevitably go with it]

"leaving you was the dumbest thing i ever did, and all i've wanted for the past year is a second chance, i never thought it was possible.i thought you hated me, you had every right to. i'm amazed you don't, i think i would have just let this go, no matter how much i still loved you"

" i love you and i think you love me,what we decide to do about it remains a matter for some discussion"

["it was wonderful and you know it. and do you know why? because we loved each other."he said.
"no" , she replied, "we used to love eash other, we don't even know each other now, we're practically strangers again."]

"you were wonderful, thats why i loved you, i just don't want to do it again. We did it, it's over. Why screw up the good memories with more bad ones? i had almost forgotten the bad part, and now you come along and want to do it all over again. well i just can't"
